  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">11.2 Tenant's Insurance</div>
    {{#if tenant_insurance_required}}
    <p><strong>Requirement:</strong> {{tenant_insurance_required}}</p>
    {{else}}
    <p>The tenant is strongly advised to obtain contents insurance for their personal belongings.</p>
    {{/if}}

    <div class="important-box">
      <div class="important-title">‚ö†Ô∏è Important: Landlord's Insurance Does Not Cover Tenant's Belongings</div>
      <p>The landlord's insurance only covers the building and fixtures. It does NOT cover the tenant's furniture, personal possessions, or liability. Tenants should obtain their own contents and liability insurance.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- COMPREHENSIVE TERMS & CONDITIONS -->
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-number">12</span>
    COMPREHENSIVE TERMS & CONDITIONS
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">12.1 Assignment & Subletting</div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.1.1</span>
      The tenant shall not assign, sublet, or part with possession of the whole or any part of the property without the landlord's written consent. Such consent shall not be unreasonably withheld.
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.1.2</span>
      In Scotland, tenants have a statutory right to request permission to sublet or take in lodgers under Section 14 of the Private Housing (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">12.2 Alterations & Improvements</div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.2.1</span>
      The tenant shall not make any alterations, additions, or improvements to the property without the landlord's prior written consent.
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.2.2</span>
      <strong>Right to Change:</strong> The landlord may make reasonable changes to the property, fixtures, or fittings during the tenancy, provided:
      <ul>
        <li>Reasonable notice is given (normally 28 days)</li>
        <li>Changes do not substantially affect the tenant's enjoyment of the property</li>
        <li>Essential items are replaced with equivalent or better quality items</li>
        <li>The tenant's quiet enjoyment is respected</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.2.3</span>
      Any improvements made by the tenant become the property of the landlord at the end of the tenancy unless otherwise agreed in writing.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">12.3 Use of Property</div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.3.1</span>
      The property must be used as the tenant's only or principal home and for residential purposes only.
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.3.2</span>
      The tenant shall not use the property for any illegal, immoral, or antisocial purpose.
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.3.3</span>
      The tenant shall not operate any business from the property without the landlord's prior written consent.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">12.4 Nuisance & Antisocial Behaviour</div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.4.1</span>
      The tenant shall not cause nuisance, annoyance, or disturbance to neighbours or other occupiers in the vicinity.
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.4.2</span>
      The tenant is responsible for the behaviour of all persons (including visitors) at the property.
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.4.3</span>
      Antisocial behaviour is grounds for eviction under the Private Housing (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">12.5 Refuse & Recycling</div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.5.1</span>
      The tenant must dispose of refuse in accordance with local council requirements.
    </div>
    {{#if recycling_bins}}
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.5.2</span>
      ‚úì Recycling bins are provided. The tenant must use them in accordance with local recycling guidelines.
    </div>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">12.6 Data Protection & Privacy</div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.6.1</span>
      The landlord will process the tenant's personal data in accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018.
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.6.2</span>
      Personal data will be used only for purposes related to the tenancy and will be kept secure.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">12.7 End of Tenancy</div>
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.7.1</span>
      At the end of the tenancy, the tenant must:
      <ul>
        <li>Return the property in the same condition as at the start (fair wear and tear excepted)</li>
        <li>Remove all personal belongings</li>
        <li>Return all keys, fobs, and access devices</li>
        <li>Provide forwarding address for deposit return</li>
        <li>Settle all outstanding bills</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    {{#if decoration_condition}}
    <div class="clause">
      <span class="clause-number">12.7.2</span>
      <strong>Decoration Standard:</strong> {{decoration_condition}}
    </div>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">12.8 Notice to End Tenancy</div>
    <div class="scotland-legal-box">
      <div class="scotland-legal-title">Ending a PRT in Scotland</div>
      <p><strong>Tenant Giving Notice:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum 28 days' notice in writing</li>
        <li>Notice must be in the prescribed Scottish Government form</li>
        <li>Rent is payable until the end of the notice period</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Landlord Ending Tenancy:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Must have one of the 18 grounds for eviction specified in the Act</li>
        <li>Must apply to the First-tier Tribunal for Scotland</li>
        <li>Cannot simply give notice - tribunal approval required</li>
        <li>Different notice periods apply depending on the ground (28-84 days minimum)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  {{#if additional_terms}}
  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">12.9 Additional Terms</div>
    <p>{{additional_terms}}</p>
  </div>
  {{/if}}

  <!-- SECTION 13: DISPUTE RESOLUTION -->
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-number">13</span>
    DISPUTE RESOLUTION
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">13.1 First-tier Tribunal for Scotland</div>
    <p>Disputes relating to this tenancy are resolved by the <strong>First-tier Tribunal for Scotland (Housing and Property Chamber)</strong>.</p>

    <div class="explainer-box">
      <div class="explainer-title">
        <span class="explainer-icon">‚öñÔ∏è</span>
        Tenant Rights & Dispute Resolution
      </div>
      <p>The tenant can apply to the Tribunal for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Failure to carry out repairs (breach of Repairing Standard)</li>
        <li>Wrongful termination of tenancy</li>
        <li>Unlawful rent increases</li>
        <li>Failure to protect deposit</li>
        <li>Unlawful eviction or harassment</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Contact:</strong> Housing and Property Chamber<br>
      <strong>Website:</strong> housingandpropertychamber.scot</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">13.2 Rent Disputes</div>
    <p>If the tenant believes a rent increase is unfair, they can refer it to a Rent Officer within 21 days of receiving notice.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 14: NOTICES -->
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-number">14</span>
    NOTICES & COMMUNICATIONS
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">14.1 Method of Service</div>
    <p>Any notice or communication required under this agreement must be:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>In writing</li>
      <li>Delivered by hand, by email, or by recorded delivery post</li>
      <li>Using the contact details specified in this agreement</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <div class="subsection-title">14.2 Change of Details</div>
    <p>Both parties must notify each other promptly of any change in contact details (address, email, phone number).</p>
  </div>

